    <p>At least one in six house­holds in Sin­ga­pore shops for gro­ceries with­out ever leav­ing their homes. With the click of a few but­tons, ev­ery­thing you need - from frozen meats and toi­let pa­per to xi­aobaicai and av­o­ca­dos, can be de­liv­ered to your doorstep in a mat­ter of days.</p>
    <p>What hap­pens be­hind the scenes at the ware­house of RedMart to get your or­der to your doorstep safely? The Sun­day Times looks at how the on­line gro­cery plat­form uses data sci­ence to fore­cast con­sumer de­mand and puts in place stor­age measures to min­imise food wastage.</p>

